    <objects>
        <objectClass>
            <name>HLAobjectRoot</name>
            <objectClass>
                <name>DIM_HazardRegion</name>
                <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                <semantics>The geographical region of a hazard in a synthetic environment.</semantics>
                <attribute>
                    <name>Time</name>
                    <dataType>ScenarioTime</dataType>
                    <updateType>Static</updateType>
                    <updateCondition>NA</updateCondition>
                    <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                    <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                    <transportation>HLAbestEffort</transportation>
                    <order>Receive</order>
                    <semantics>Time at which the hazard region was first created.</semantics>
                </attribute>
                <attribute>
                    <name>Area</name>
                    <dataType>LocationStructArray</dataType>
                    <updateType>Conditional</updateType>
                    <updateCondition>On change</updateCondition>
                    <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                    <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                    <transportation>HLAbestEffort</transportation>
                    <order>Receive</order>
                    <semantics>Required: Geographical boundary of the HazardRegion.</semantics>
                </attribute>
                <objectClass>
                    <name>Flooding</name>
                    <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                    <semantics>Representation of a flooded area.</semantics>
                    <attribute>
                        <name>Level</name>
                        <dataType>MeterFloat32</dataType>
                        <updateType>Conditional</updateType>
                        <updateCondition>On change</updateCondition>
                        <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAbestEffort</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>FloodingLevel represents the water level of the flooding relative to Mean Sea Level (MSL).</semantics>
                    </attribute>
                    <attribute>
                        <name>LevelChange</name>
                        <dataType>LevelChangeMeterPerSecondFloat32</dataType>
                        <updateType>Conditional</updateType>
                        <updateCondition>On change</updateCondition>
                        <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAbestEffort</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>FloodingLevelChange represents the change of the water level over time. An observer thus can determine if the flood level is going to rise (and further actions/precautions may be necessary) or if the water is draining and thus recovery measure can start soon.</semantics>
                    </attribute>
                </objectClass>
                <objectClass>
                    <name>Wildfire</name>
                    <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                    <semantics>Representation of a wildfire that may spread.</semantics>
                    <attribute>
                        <name>FrontWidth</name>
                        <dataType>MeterFloat32</dataType>
                        <updateType>Conditional</updateType>
                        <updateCondition>On change</updateCondition>
                        <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAbestEffort</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>Required: FrontWidth indicates the thickness of the actual fire ring surrounding a no longer burning region. It is assumed that a fire start at one or more spots and then spreads in a circular shape with a fire front of certain thickness and burnt land behind the front line. The Area attribute from DiM_HazardRegion defines the outer boundary of the overall region, the front of flames in the denoted thickness is assumed to extend from inside the boundary into the region.</semantics>
                    </attribute>
                    <attribute>
                        <name>FrontVelocity</name>
                        <dataType>VelocityMeterPerSecondFloat32</dataType>
                        <updateType>Conditional</updateType>
                        <updateCondition>On change</updateCondition>
                        <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAbestEffort</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>Optional: FrontVelocity denotes the spread velocity of the front line. Thus, an observer can estimate when the fire will hit a certain location. The actual boundary and the velocity hereby have the same relationship as position and velocity of a physical entity, although here in a simplifying assumption only one single speed of spreading is assumed to hold. Default = 0.</semantics>
                    </attribute>
                    <attribute>
                        <name>Temperature</name>
                        <dataType>TemperatureDegreeCelsiusFloat32</dataType>
                        <updateType>Conditional</updateType>
                        <updateCondition>On change</updateCondition>
                        <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAreliable</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>Optional: Temperature, based on SI derived unit degree Celsius, unit symbol Â°C.</semantics>
                    </attribute>
                </objectClass>
                <objectClass>
                    <name>EarthquakeArea</name>
                    <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                    <semantics>An area affected by an earthquake.</semantics>
                    <attribute>
                        <name>Magnitude</name>
                        <dataType>RichterScale</dataType>
                        <updateType>Conditional</updateType>
                        <updateCondition>On change</updateCondition>
                        <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAbestEffort</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>Required: Richter magnitude scale.</semantics>
                    </attribute>
                </objectClass>
                <objectClass>
                    <name>Landslide</name>
                    <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                    <semantics>Representation of a landslide area covered by mud, snow or gravel.</semantics>
                    <attribute>
                        <name>Thickness</name>
                        <dataType>MeterFloat32</dataType>
                        <updateType>Conditional</updateType>
                        <updateCondition>On change</updateCondition>
                        <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAbestEffort</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>Required: Thickness in meter.</semantics>
                    </attribute>
                    <attribute>
                        <name>LandslideType</name>
                        <dataType>LandslideTypeEnum</dataType>
                        <updateType>NA</updateType>
                        <updateCondition></updateCondition>
                        <ownership>DivestAcquire</ownership>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAreliable</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>Optional: The type of landslide material. Default = 0.</semantics>
                    </attribute>
                </objectClass>
            </objectClass>
            <objectClass>
                <name>EnvironmentObject</name>
                <objectClass>
                    <name>LinearObject</name>
                    <objectClass>
                        <name>BreachableLinearObject</name>
                        <objectClass>
                            <name>Levee</name>
                            <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                            <semantics>A levee is a wall/separator that protects an area from flooding.</semantics>
                        </objectClass>
                        <objectClass>
                            <name>Firebreak</name>
                            <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                            <semantics>A firebreak is a corridor without any burning things. The firebreak should separate the burning part from the not burning part.</semantics>
                        </objectClass>
                    </objectClass>
                </objectClass>
            </objectClass>
        </objectClass>
    </objects>
    <interactions>
        <interactionClass>
            <name>HLAinteractionRoot</name>
            <interactionClass>
                <name>ETR_Root</name>
                <interactionClass>
                    <name>ETR_Task</name>
                    <interactionClass>
                        <name>PumpFlooding</name>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAreliable</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>Task an entity to start pumping water out of an area.</semantics>
                        <parameter>
                            <name>FloodingId</name>
                            <dataType>UUID</dataType>
                            <semantics>Required: Reference to a Flooding object.</semantics>
                        </parameter>
                        <parameter>
                            <name>Duration</name>
                            <dataType>TimeMillisecondInt64</dataType>
                            <semantics>Optional: The duration of the pumping task. Default if not provided pumping shall continue until explicit task cancel or beginning of next task.</semantics>
                        </parameter>
                    </interactionClass>
                    <interactionClass>
                        <name>ExtinguishWildfire</name>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAreliable</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>Task an entity to extinguish a wildfire.</semantics>
                        <parameter>
                            <name>WildfireId</name>
                            <dataType>UUID</dataType>
                            <semantics>Required: A reference to a Wildfire object.</semantics>
                        </parameter>
                    </interactionClass>
                    <interactionClass>
                        <name>Engineering</name>
                        <interactionClass>
                            <name>CreateFireBreak</name>
                            <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                            <transportation>HLAreliable</transportation>
                            <order>Receive</order>
                            <semantics>Task for building up a firebreak.</semantics>
                        </interactionClass>
                        <interactionClass>
                            <name>CreateLevee</name>
                            <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                            <transportation>HLAbestEffort</transportation>
                            <order>Receive</order>
                            <semantics>Task for building up a levee.</semantics>
                        </interactionClass>
                    </interactionClass>
                    <interactionClass>
                        <name>Evacuate</name>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAreliable</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>A request for evacuation</semantics>
                        <parameter>
                            <name>Area</name>
                            <dataType>LocationStructArray</dataType>
                            <semantics>Required: The geographical area in which evacuation takes place.</semantics>
                        </parameter>
                        <parameter>
                            <name>EntityType</name>
                            <dataType>EntityTypeStruct</dataType>
                            <semantics>Required: Type of entity. Based on the Entity Type record as specified in IEEE 1278.1-1995 section 5.2.16.</semantics>
                        </parameter>
                        <parameter>
                            <name>Amount</name>
                            <dataType>QuantityInt32</dataType>
                            <semantics>Optional: How many persons / things to evacuate. Default = All.</semantics>
                        </parameter>
                    </interactionClass>
                </interactionClass>
                <interactionClass>
                    <name>ETR_Report</name>
                    <interactionClass>
                        <name>HazardObservation</name>
                        <sharing>PublishSubscribe</sharing>
                        <transportation>HLAreliable</transportation>
                        <order>Receive</order>
                        <semantics>Observation of a dangerous area.</semantics>
                        <parameter>
                            <name>Area</name>
                            <dataType>LocationStructArray</dataType>
                            <semantics>Required: The estimated area affected by the hazard.</semantics>
                        </parameter>
                        <parameter>
                            <name>HazardType</name>
                            <dataType>HazardTypeEnum</dataType>
                            <semantics>Required: The type of hazard obeserved.</semantics>
                        </parameter>
                    </interactionClass>
                </interactionClass>
            </interactionClass>
        </interactionClass>
    </interactions>
    <dataTypes>
